{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609304","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609304"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:44:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:44:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16099"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16099","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16099"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.06,0.32,0.26,0.23]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8790"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71216"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8790","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8790"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16099"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56690"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1540"},{"type":"tags","id":"1636"},{"type":"tags","id":"1652"},{"type":"tags","id":"2105"},{"type":"tags","id":"4133"},{"type":"tags","id":"4758"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20986"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20989"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71216","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71216"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents two months after evacuation of a complete hydatidiform mole. She reports irregular vaginal bleeding and blood-stained discharge. Her serum human chorionic gonadotropin level is rising. Choriocarcinoma is suspected.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following represents the most common pattern of metastatic spread in choriocarcinoma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Vagina and bone marrow","Liver and brain","Lungs and liver","Vagina and liver","Lungs and vagina"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EChoriocarcinoma most commonly spreads to the \u003Cstrong\u003Elungs and vagina\u003C/strong\u003E. The lungs are involved in approximately 80% of cases with metastatic disease, while vaginal metastases occur in about 30% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther patterns of spread are less common:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVagina and bone marrow\u003C/strong\u003E - While vaginal spread is common, bone marrow involvement is rare\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver and brain\u003C/strong\u003E - These are sites of poor prognosis but are less commonly involved\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELungs and liver\u003C/strong\u003E - While lung metastases are common, liver involvement is less frequent\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVagina and liver\u003C/strong\u003E - Liver metastases are less common than lung involvement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe tendency for early haematogenous spread reflects the origin of choriocarcinoma from trophoblastic tissue, which has direct access to maternal blood vessels. Despite its metastatic nature, choriocarcinoma generally responds well to chemotherapy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Gestational trophoblastic neoplasia most commonly metastasises to the lungs (80%) and vagina (30%).","Early haematogenous spread is characteristic of choriocarcinoma due to its origin from trophoblastic tissue with direct access to maternal blood vessels."],"references":["Duffy L, Zhang L, Sheath K, Love DR, George AM. The Diagnosis of Choriocarcinoma in Molar Pregnancies: A Revised Approach in Clinical Testing. J Clin Med Res. 2015 Dec;7(12):961-6. doi: 10.14740/jocmr2236w. Epub 2015 Oct 23. PMID: 26566410; PMCID: PMC4625817.","Ghassemzadeh S, Farci F, Kang M. Hydatidiform Mole. [Updated 2023 May 22]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459155/","Singh S, Sardhana M, Sharma S, Chitralkar P. Choriocarcinoma presenting as an isolated bone marrow metastasis-a case report. Ecancermedicalscience. 2014 Jan 29;8:393. doi: 10.3332/ecancer.2014.393. PMID: 24605133; PMCID: PMC3907403.","Singh S, Sardhana M, Sharma S, Chitralkar P. Choriocarcinoma presenting as an isolated bone marrow metastasis-a case report. Ecancermedicalscience. 2014 Jan 29;8:393. doi: 10.3332/ecancer.2014.393. PMID: 24605133; PMCID: PMC3907403."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56690"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16099"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56690","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56690"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-17T20:37:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-17T20:38:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8790"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71216"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici